# LLM Wiki

This is a wiki maintained by an LLM following the
[llm-wiki skill](https://gist.github.com/karpathy/442a6bf555914893e9891c11519de94f)
pattern. It re-organizes knowledge from the project's raw sources by **concept**
rather than by source, with cross-linked pages and an append-only operation log.

## Layout

```
wiki/
├── SKILL.md     ← you are here (the wiki's maintenance manual)
├── index.md     ← catalog of all pages
├── log.md       ← append-only operation log
├── concept/     ← concept pages
├── entity/      ← named entities
├── summary/     ← one page per ingested raw source
├── compare/     ← comparison pages
└── synthesis/   ← narrative cross-cutting summaries
```

## Schema (rules for the LLM)

### Page types

- **concept** — an idea, mechanism, or pattern (e.g. `attention.md`)
- **entity** — a named thing: model, person, dataset, system (e.g. `transformer.md`)
- **summary** — one per raw source; filename matches the source slug
- **compare** — two-or-more-way comparison (e.g. `attention-vs-rnn.md`)
- **synthesis** — narrative spanning many pages (e.g. `overview.md`)

A page's type is fixed once chosen.

### Filenames

- ASCII, lowercase, kebab-case
- Singular nouns where possible
- No type prefix in the filename — the directory encodes it
- The H1 inside the file may be in any language

### Page structure (required)

```markdown
# <Display Title>

> **Type:** concept | entity | summary | compare | synthesis
> **Aliases:** alt-1, alt-2  (optional)
> **Related:** [Other](../entity/other.md)

## <First section>

...prose...

## Sources

- [<source-slug>](../summary/<source-slug>.md) — page X
```

### Cross-references

Standard relative markdown links. Every link target must exist.

### index.md

One section per page type, alphabetical within each section. Each entry is
one line: link + 8-15 word description. Regenerated on every ingest.

### log.md

Append-only. ISO-8601 timestamp prefix. Operation prefixes: `ingest`, `lint`, `query`.

## Workflows

### Ingest

Two passes:
1. **Plan** — given new content + index, decide which pages to create/update
2. **Apply** — for each operation, write or rewrite the full page

Then regenerate `index.md` and append to `log.md`.

### Query

Two passes:
1. **Pick pages** — given the question + index, choose which pages to read
2. **Answer** — read those pages and answer the question

Small wikis (under ~2000 tokens) can skip Pass 1 and dump all pages.

### Lint

Reports contradictions, stale claims, orphan pages, broken links, duplicates,
and misclassified pages. Does not auto-fix.

## You can edit this file

This SKILL.md is the wiki's own maintenance manual. The LLM reads it on
every operation. Edit the rules above to adjust conventions for **this**
specific wiki — the changes take effect immediately and travel with the
wiki directory.
